messages.content: Selle wakes up in a chair at an unfamiliar table. Donald is distracted reading a book across from him.

*Ugh... What the hell was that dream...*
Selle is alert to the fact that they are in a completely unfamiliar place, and sitting at a table. 
*Where the hell am I? I fell asleep on Laura's couch. I must have been dragged somewhere while I was asleep.*
Selle notices that Donald is across from them.
"Ugh... What's going on here?"
"Morning." Donald tosses aside the Wazy Emerson book. "The boss wants to speak with you and that fixer of yours made me carry you instead of waking you up. Kooky bitch."

*Really not the best experience waking up somewhere other than where you fell asleep. That dream must have put me in a real deep sleep for me to not wake up being carried. Setting that aside, the boss? I guess I'll see what happens.*
"Yeah, sure. I'll speak with him."
"Just don’t set him off, okay? He *will* kill you and then I’ll have to be the one to clean up your mess."
"Haha... I'll do my best."
"The Queen of the Night and the leader of the Faceless will be there too. Are you familiar with them?"

*What's with the high ranking entourage? The Queen of Night especially is someone who is incredibly difficult to find out any information about. Definitely not a good sign. I can't exactly refuse though.*
Selle breathes a deep sigh.
"Yeah, I'm familiar with them."
*I guess I'll find out why they're all here soon.*
Donald gets up. “Alright, follow me.”

*Where the hell are we, anyway? This is so fishy...*
Selle stands up and follows Donald, looking around and trying to understand where they are in the meantime.
((Roll perception ig))
(Bruh. Nat1
Selle has no idea if they’re even still in Soltaria.

They enter a large room. There are 4 chairs, seemingly one for each leader of the hellhounds. The 2 leaders Donald mentioned are seated at their respective spots. At the back of the room is a large throne of a pitch black colour, seemingly constructed out of weapons that have been welded together. The Endless Eclipse rests on it.

Donald gives a polite bow and takes his own seat.

*Wow this is definitely not intimidating at all yeah... What kind of place even is this? How do you make this and have people just not know it exists. I have way too many questions. I just need to follow what's going on, I suppose.*
Selle bows, visibly a little confused. They look around the room and try to discern the mood of everyone.
The Eclipse leaves his throne and approaches Selle. "Yule, correct? I am the undying man known as the devil of Soltaria."

*Friendlier than expected.*
"Yes, I am Yule. It's a pleasure to meet you."
"Tell me what happened to my boy, Locruz."

*Locruz... Laura told me what happened to him... I'm glad he's alive.*
Selle starts to recall their memories and say what happened.
"Yesterday, I went with him and one other person to investigate what had happened to Destiny's members. We were told that the person with the most information about what happened was Major Iono Wilkinson. Locruz led us to his house and the Major told us to fight him to get the information we needed. During the fight, Locruz was knocked out onto the street and was unconscious. Apparently, Iono had tipped off the church that we were there and sent Harriet Dana Edwardson and a group of priests to try and... subjugate us. Myself and another person had to use a spell to escape, but Locruz was far from us and wasn't conscious. Only yesterday had I heard that Locruz is fine but being held by the Order. That's the extent of my knowledge."
*That kid... always getting into the worst situations. Damn it.*
"Ha." He grabs Yule’s shoulder with a terrifyingly firm hand. "You’re well-informed. I don’t need to explain why that’s a problem, do I?"

*Guh... What a pain... Maybe I need to cut down on the explanations sometimes...*
Selle face twitches a bit.
"...Kgh... What are you getting at?"
"You’re going to bring him back to us. Or I’ll kill you right now." The Eclipse chuckles happily.

*The snowball just keeps rolling down the hill. Everything is always fucking trouble.*
Selle winces.
".......Fine."

"Good. Do whatever you want to bring him back, just keep us out of it. No relying on Donald’s poor joke at generosity." The Eclipse.

"Sir, I have a question for him as well." The Queen smirks.

*Keep them out of it, huh.*
Selle looks towards the direction of the Queen, waiting for the question.
*Probably the most frightening person here. There's not much I know about her, compared to everyone else.*

"I don’t believe for a second you stabbed the emperor. You’d have the most to lose from his replacements, wouldn’t you?" The Queen smiles as she approaches. "No… The emperor you attacked… It was the acting emperor, wasn’t it? That’s the error in the high priestess’s divination. Am I wrong?"

"I shouldn't be surprised that you know so much. Divination? Sounds like a whole bunch of shit. Of course it's wrong. I don't even know who killed the Emperor... In other words, you are absolutely correct."
Selle grimaces in disgust and looks away as she remembers Asturian's  face.
*Scary lady. She knows everything. But, this gives me a lot of information. Someone's put "Selle"'s face out there as the killer of the Emperor. Poor book publishing companies.*

"To be clear, uh… That wasn’t us either. Even Linjamin’s not that stupid. If anyone here knows anything, it’s the queen and she’s not talking." Donald.

Linjamin remains silent.

"You were at the party too, weren’t you Yule? I know what Asturian’s attacker looks like… And I saw him at the party too." The Queen.

*Feels weird for someone to refer to me in 3rd person...*
"There's no point beating around the bush with you. Yes, I was at the party."

"Huh!?" Donald.

"That’ll be all." She sits back down smugly.

*No matter what I said, I was only confirming information she already knew anyway.*
Selle sighs and shakes her head.

Linjamin gets up. "Is everyone done then?"

Donald and the queen nod.

"Go ahead, Linjamin." Eclipse.

*This is really turning into a straight up interrogation now.*
Selle is alert.

"Sorry, but we can’t let you know the route here." Linjamin grabs Selle’s face with shocking speed and magically knocks them out.

Selle wakes up in a garbage dump in the slums of the city. Their head hurts.

"Ugh..."
*At least it's over. Could have picked a better place to stick me in, though.*
Selle feels their arm in immense, burning pain, paired with a massive headache. They wince in immense pain and feel that that arm has lost feeling. Before Selle can even acknowledge their surroundings, they grab an emergency pill from their inner vest pocket and swallow it.
*I went way too long without medicine. So much time spent unconscious is bad... and this place stinks.*

*Locruz... I guess he would probably be held at the main church in Soltaria... What would they even be doing with him? Laura joked about converting him to be a youth pastor or something but they are probably just trying to use him to get information about me.*
Selle stands up and looks around.
No one seems to be around. It's a very secluded spot.

*They know my face. I need to create a disguise, and a new name.*
Selle reaches into their inventory to take out a disguise kit. It contains make-up, hair dye, and various coloured contact lenses. This is what they used to create the "Selle" disguise.
*Maybe a young lady would be a good disguise. It would be, the easiest... As for a name, I'll pick something familiar, and simple. Something like, Elyssa. It's close enough to my real name but not so much that it's the same. I can use a blonde wig, and wear brown contacts. The only thing I need is a change of clothes and a bath.  I only have this black jacket at the moment, but I've got 15 gil to my name. Should be feasable.*
They have applied the contacts and let their hair down instead of tying it up, but have decided to not put the wig on yet. They still have a very androgynous appearance.
After this, Selle tries to figure out which part of the slums they are in and how far they are from a clothes dealer and an inn.
They can go to those places without much issue. Though it would be a clothes store and not a clothes dealer, which sounds like a crime somehow.
Selle brushes themselves off and heads towards an inn.
"Hello?" Innkeeper.
It's morning, to be clear.
"Could I book a single bed room for 4 hours, please."
"Sure. That'll be 2sp."
Selle pays the cost.
Selle has acquired a room.
Selle goes to the room, and takes a bath.
Aeolian wakes up in his bed.

I yawn, and arise, checking my notes.

Following this, I head out to my nourishment room to secure nourishment.
Theo is waiting for him in the nourishment room. "Good morning, sir!"

“Morning.” This man is truly the emperor of being in my house. “Hope you’re well.” I grumble, brewing a Caffeinated Beverage.

> Don’t even TALK to me before I’ve had my Caffeinated Beverage.
- Wazy Emerson
"Yes, sir." He nods.
“Mhm. Anything on the itinerary? I agreed informally to meet with Aliza this morning, of course…”
"I don't believe so, sir! Oh, um... They said we should go to the temple today to speak with Mr Klezmer."

“Ah, yes, right.” I sip my beverage.

> I can’t remember shit that was three weeks ago damn
- Rean Descartes
"You know him well, right sir?"
“Reasonably. He’s a kind young lad.”
"Would he really have anything to do with the emperor’s attacker, then?"
“I don’t personally think so, but it’s possible.”
"So you don’t believe the high priestess’s claim?" He makes a mental note of this as someone knocks at the door.
“The claim of the woman who barged in and blew up a building? Not taking it at face value, no.” I sigh, and open the door.
It’s Aliza. "Good morning, Ally."
“Morning. I had a most unusual dream.”
"Well, you have always been quite the dreamer." Aliza.
“Perhaps so. I am untethered by the limits of many others.” I shake my head. “The dream seemed a warning, or a hint… at any rate, I was next going to speak with the man apprehended yesterday.”
"Who?"
“Locruz Klezmer.” I answer promptly and without delay.

"Who's that?" Aliza.

"The man who was apprehended yesterday." Theo.
“Yess. He lives around here. Nice kid.”
"Why did he get arrested then?" Aliza.
“That is what I wish to discern.”
"I see." Aliza nods.
“Would you like to accompany this endeavor?”
"If it’s relevant."
“It should be. Libra seems to believe this already solves everything. And if she’s just very confidently wrong, understanding why is still useful.”
"I see." Aliza nods.
I exit my home.
They follow.
“It’s an absurd overreach of power, regardless of veracity.” I shake my head, heading over to the indicated location.

They arrive at the temple. The Duchess exits it in front of them. "…Hello, Baron. …And you would be Washington’s daughter?"

Aliza nods. "It’s a pleasure to see you, Duchess."
“Mrm.” I abstain from the pleasantries, nodding at her.
Nash wakes up, alive once more. An unfamiliar priest, the duchess, and Harriet Dana Edwardson are here.
"Gghh-" He makes a sputtering sound of shock, jerking upwards. "Ah... 'M awake. Alive? Y-eaaaah." He's still a little out of it.

"Welcome back, Nash." The Duchess.

The priest leaves, seeing this was successful.

"Libra has guided your soul back to us." Harriet.
"Er... yes." He says. "Thank you both, for uh, your continued investment." A moment. "In me." He clarifies.
He begins doing the fucking 👉 👈 thing while looking to the side. "Is it customary, um, for those who were revived, to speak of visions?"

"Yes, I would assume hallucinations are common when your brain is being magically pressed back together." The Duchess.

Harriet ignores her, looking at Nash with a serious expression. "You saw the afterlife, then?"
"Something like that, yes." Nash says, staring dazed into the distance, too shaken to even antagonize Harriet as usual.

"I’ve been there once too." Harriet clenches her first, her hand shaking lightly.

The Duchess reacts with a sort of knowing smirk, like she’s enjoying a good practical joke.

Nash, um... doesn't know what his mother is doing. Is she signaling something to him, maybe...? Looking at her warped smile, like she knows a secret, it's as if he's being mocked. Which is dumb, obviously. He's misreading the situation.

And h-hey, why's Harriet responding like that? All furrowed brow, as if she *understands*... it's not the same. It couldn't have been the same experience, surely. It's not like Harriet, uh, needs.. whatever. Is she mocking him too?
"And what did youuuuu see?" Nash drawls, raising an eyebrow. *Tell me something stupid, or made up! Y-yeah.*

"…" Harriet goes silent and closes her remaining eye. She breathes shakily.

"Yes, I had to save her once too. Unfortunately that eye of hers was unsalvageable for whatever reason. At least your eyes still work, Nash." The Duchess.
"Yes." Nash says proudly. "That's one thing I've still got going for me." He smirks.
"You wear glasses." Harriet scoffs. "I have work for you, Nash."
Nash reaches up to touch his glasses self-consciously, then shakes it off. "Well.. fine. What is it?"
"We’ve captured a member of the hellhounds, the leader of their street gang called Destiny. He’s working with the emperor’s attacker. But refuses to tell us who."
Nash scoffs. "And you can't just torture him?"
"…He’s resilient. Regardless, we’re using him as bait now. I want you to guard him."
"GUARD him?" Nash says, disbelieving. "From what..? Killing himself?"
"From the actual attacker who will come to save him, Nash. That is what bait means."
"Ohhh, that makes sense."
"I’ll leave you 2 to it, then." The Duchess smiles and leaves.
"Right." Nash says.
He wraps his arms around himself and scowls up at Harriet.
"Your comrades are already watching him. Follow me." Harriet walks down a corridor.
Alright. Sure!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Urgh. He doesn't even know why he's so mad right now. It's a pointless emotion.
Nash gets up and follows her.

They arrive at a large room containing a cell in the center. This room would normally be used for ritual purposes to punish criminals in the name of libra. Inside is a young man who looks younger than Nash. 

Ruth notices him with a slight smile. Orion rushes over to him. "You’re back!"

Nash moves to him too. What do you even say in this sort of situation...? *Sorry, I really wanted to die back there. I thought we had all agreed on the importance of that. Why are you happy that I'm here? I shouldn't be happy for that.*
He smiles faintly. "Yes."

"You’re lucky your parents are rich. I wouldn’t have the cash for those sorts of resurrection rituals." Orion.

"That thing got away because of your reckless death." Ruth.
Nash allows his smile to become fuller. "Sorry for dying in pursuit of victory, I suppose."

"Pursuit of victory implies that accomplished anything. Grow up." Ruth punches his shoulder. 

"Is this place’s entire government this batshit?" Teenager in jail.
Nash turns to the kid, rolling his eyes. "What would you know, degenerate?"

"The eclipse totally owns you guys." Teen.

Harriet leaves.
Nash does the get-a-load-of-this-guy point in the kid's general direction, but otherwise ignores him.

"Do you feel like telling us yet who stabbed the emperor?" Ruth.

"I told you it wasn’t us, you idiots!" Teen.
Nash just laughs. "Stop being moronic. We know it's you."

"Don’t you guys think this was Linjamin? I mean even ignoring the fact he’s not that stupid I don’t even work with him!" Teen.

"So you’ll give us a list of associates you do work with, then?" Ruth.

He shuts up.
Nash leans against the wall, fixing the teen with a stare.
Orion heads over next to Nash. "How was it? …Dying, I mean."

Nash exhales, looking at his hands. "Um.. a little weird." He says quietly, deliberately trying to keep Ruth and the other teen out of the conversation. "I mean, it's all fuzzy now, but. I really think I saw *Her.*" He tries to inject an appropriate amount of gravitas into the word.
"Your mom?"
Nash blinks. "What? No. Why would I...? I mean my goddess, obviously." *Why would he think that? Hah, what? Huh?*
"Oh… Libra?"
"Yeah."
"What was she like?"
Nash hesitates. "...Warm. And a little stern. But in a well-intentioned way, I think."
"It was nice." He admits. *Not all of it, obviously. And I didn't like. You know, the going.*
"I… see."
*Fuck, was that a weird thing to say? I don't think it's weird...! It's a normal response to meeting your goddess. Don't judge me, Oriooooonnnnn....*
Nash crosses his arms. "I was in awe, of course. So we didn't exchange many words." Nash blinks. "How did the situation with the intruders and the.. *creature* resolve itself, after my death?"
"We just kind of ran. Haven't heard anything about it since. The order said they'd look into it though."

"Makes sense." Nash nods. "Well... thanks for retrieving my body, I suppose." *Even if I'd rather you didn't. Haha, why didn't you just leave me behind...? Did you not think that was a suitable death for me?*
"Do you think that thing was... Human?"
He frowns. "I'm not sure. It had a human face, and certainly vocalized, but the proportions, eugh. I really don't know."
"Think it could be one of those mutants?"
Nash's face spasms briefly. "May..be. That kind of savagery would be, uh, *characteristic* of them." *Disgusting.*
"Makes sense. I've never heard of that kind of mutation though."
Nash braces a hand against the bottom of his chin, lost in thought. "Me neither."
At this point, Aeolian enters. ((End session sorry Penny left hours ago and never returned))
